buyWithBNB().details: Allows users to purchase Seesea tokens using BNB.

buyWithOtherTokens(address,uint256).details: Allows users to purchase Seesea tokens using supported tokens (e.g., USDT, USDC).

params.amount: The amount of the supported token to spend.
params.token: The address of the supported token.

constructor.details: Constructor that initializes the contract with the initial owner, price feed address, and supported tokens.

params._priceFeedAddress: The address of the Chainlink price feed.
params._usdc: The address of the USDC token.
params._usdt: The address of the USDT token.
params.initialOwner: The initial owner of the contract.

getBNBUSDTPrice().details: Retrieves the BNB price in USDT using the Chainlink price feed.

returns._0: The BNB price in USDT with 18 decimals.

getMinBNBForPurchase().details: Calculates the minimum BNB required for a purchase based on the current BNB price in USDT.

returns._0: The minimum BNB required for a purchase.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdrawBNB().details: Allows the owner to withdraw BNB from the contract.

withdrawTokens(uint256,address).details: Allows the owner to withdraw supported tokens from the contract.

params.amount: The amount of the supported token to withdraw.
params.token: The address of the supported token.
